jejunal diverticula are an uncommon acquired disease that is usually silent and asymptomaticwhen symptomatic they present with chronic nonspecific symptoms like pain nausea malnutrition and sometimes with acute presentation like gastrointestinal hemorrhage peritonitis and obstructionthe majority of complications seen as an acute abdomen similar to appendicitis cholecystitis or colonic diverticulitis but they also may appear with atypical symptomswe are presenting a 63yearold male reported in emergency with painful abdomen and diagnosed as having peritonitison laparotomy we incidentally found giant and multiple jejunal diverticula along with ileal perforationnothing was done to the jejunal diverticula as these were multiple and nonobstructivein the followup of 16 months the patient was doing welljejunoileal diverticulosis is a rare condition that continues to present formidable challenges in diagnosis and treatment